    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-12-09T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-12-09T20:00:00-05:00" n="513"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d513">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/12–1045: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stevens</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-10T09:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 10, 1945—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 10—6 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>More than 200 former puppets arrested by [the National Government?] at Peiping
                    6th and 7th December and held for trial for treason collaboration. Another
                    hundred seized Tientsin. Peiping arrests include members and former members
                    North China Political Affairs Commission: Wang Keh-min, Wang I-tang, Wang
                    Shih-ching, Wang Yin-tai [and] others. Also former Mayors Liu Yu-shu and Hsu
                    Hsiu-chih. Tientsin arrests include Chi Hsieh-yuan, former public security
                    chief, and Wen Shih-chen, puppet mayor. Foregoing officially confirmed by
                    present deputy mayor, Peiping.</p>
                <p>Sent to Chungking, repeated to Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>[<hi rend="smallcaps">Stevens</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
